verbose_text: The initiator caspase-9 is activated by the assembly of a multimeric complex (dubbed apoptosome) involving Apaf-1 and cytochrome c. Cleaved caspase-9 and -3 are activated and these effector caspases degrade a large number of cell proteins, ultimately inducing cell apoptosis.
